Name: primary polycythemia
Definition: A polycythemia that_has_material_basis in factors intrinsic to red cell precursors.

Name: plethora of newborn
Definition: A intestinal cancer that is located_in the appendix.

Name: acquired polycythemia
Definition: An opportunistic mycosis that has_material_basis_in Galactomyces geotrichum

Name: physiological polycythemia
Definition: A breast carcinoma in situ that is characterized by abundant eosinophilic apocrine cytoplasm and large nuclei. It is a variant of ductal carcinoma in situ of the breast.
Synonym: Apocrine carcinoma in situ of the breast
